        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 8 at 8:59PM CDT until August 8 at 10:00PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northern Texas County in the Panhandle of Oklahoma...

* Until 1000 PM CDT.

* At 858 PM CDT, a cluster of severe thunderstorms was located 9
miles west of Hough, or 12 miles southeast of Elkhart, moving east
at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.

* Locations impacted include...
Hooker and Hough.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
